                        <interp inst="t18551126-name-399" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SMITH</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">City policeman</hi>, 656). On the afternoon of 11th Nov., I was on duty in the Clothes exchange, Houndsditch, and saw Mr. Berger take hold of the prisoner by the sleeve, and this watch dropped from his arm—I stooped, and the prosecutor picked it up at the same time, and gave it into my hand—this is it (<hi rend="italic">produced</hi>), the ring has been twisted—I secured the prisoner.</p>
